The paper discusses the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) in Constraint Problems, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the impact of adding domain knowledge to the DNN, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The experiments performed in the paper involve controlled experiments, which is a topic in Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
